      <condition type:"AND">
        <custom_item>
          type        : RPM_CHECK
          description : "Check GDM installed"
          rpm         : "gdm-0.0.0-0"
          operator    : "gt"
          required    : YES
        </custom_item>
      </condition>

      <then>
        <if>
          <condition auto:"FAILED" type:"AND">
            <custom_item>
              type        : CMD_EXEC
              description : "Verify the screensaver is configured to be blank"
              cmd         : "/bin/gsettings get org.gnome.desktop.screensaver picture-uri"
              expect      : "^''$"
            </custom_item>

            <custom_item>
              type            : FILE_CONTENT_CHECK
              description     : "Verify that users cannot set the screensaver background"
              file            : "/etc/dconf/db/*.d/locks/*"
              regex           : "^[\\s]*/org/gnome/desktop/screensaver/picture-uri[\\s]*$"
              expect          : "^[\\s]*/org/gnome/desktop/screensaver/picture-uri[\\s]*$"
              file_required   : NO
              min_occurrences : "1"
              string_required : NO
            </custom_item>
          </condition>

          <then>
            <report type:"PASSED">
              description : "ALMA-09-001230 - AlmaLinux OS 9 must conceal, via the session lock, information previously visible on the display with a publicly viewable image."
              info        : "Setting the screensaver mode to blank-only conceals the contents of the display from passersby."
              solution    : "Configure AlmaLinux OS 9 to prevent a user from overriding the picture-uri setting for graphical user interfaces.

First, in the file \"/etc/dconf/db/local.d/00-security-settings\" add or update the following lines:

[org/gnome/desktop/screensaver]
picture-uri=''

Then, prevent user modification by adding the following line to \"/etc/dconf/db/local.d/locks/00-security-settings-lock\":

/org/gnome/desktop/screensaver/picture-uri

Update the dconf system databases:

$ dconf update"
